{"000-section": {"000-title": "PM Awas Yojana Gramin Assam \u2013 1.65 Lakh Houses to be built in 2017", "001-normal": "The selection of the beneficiaries for [Pradhan Mantri Awas Yojana \u2013 Gramin](https://sarkariyojana.com/pradhan-mantri-awas-yojana-gramin/) is being done on the basis of SECC-2011 data considering several factors and validating those through gram sabha.", "002-normal": "PMAY-G also provides a provision of a loan of up to Rs. 70000 for further extension of the house. A loan of up to Rs. 2 Lakh taken in 2017 for new home construction or extension will receive an interest subvention of 3% resulting in significant less burden of interest and less EMI\u2019s for the borrowers.", "003-normal": "IN All, [Narendra Modi on 31st December 2016](https://sarkariyojana.com/list-schemes-announced-narendra-modi-31st-december-2016/) has also announced 33% increase in the number of houses to be constructed under the rural housing scheme by the year 2022.", "004-normal": "The details and sanction details of the PMAY-G beneficiaries can be checked on [awaassoft.nic.in](https://sarkariyojana.com/awaassoft-pmay-gramin-beneficiary-details-application-status/) using the registration number or by beneficiary name, sanction number, BPL number or father/husband number."}}